1.text: Look at other vinyl sticker designs for inspiration.

2.text: Sketch out your design on paper.

3.text: Create your design on the computer using image editing software.

4.text: Open a new 8 x 11 inch (20.3 x 27.9 cm) document in your image editing software.

5.text: Paste the design you created in the new document.

6.text: Click the print preview button to see how your stickers will print.

7.text: Load your printer with 8 x 11-inch (20.3 x 27.9 cm) vinyl printer paper.

8.text: Print your design from the editing software onto a sheet of vinyl paper.

9.text: Apply an over-laminate sheet over your stickers.

10.text: Peel back the rest of the over-laminate backing slowly.

11.text: Cut out the laminated stickers from the sheet of vinyl.

12.text: Peel off the backing on your stickers to use them.
